Flaherty Says Excluding Reserves Was G-20 Concession

-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 
2011-02-19T18:26:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-19/flaherty-says-excluding-reserves-was-g-20-concession-correct-.html
(Corrects wording of quote in second paragraph.)  The Group of 20 finance ministers’
decision to exclude currency reserves from a list of indicators
of global financial imbalances was a concession to  China ,
Canadian Finance Minister  Jim Flaherty  told reporters in Paris
today.  “They did not want reserves to be included and reserves
were not included in the communiqué language,” Flaherty said.
“That and not using the specific language of current account.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
